criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ≥ 20years of age;

          -  diagnosis of first single hemispheric stroke (>6months);

          -  sedentary or insufficiently active;

          -  have adjusted activity score in the Human Activity Profile <74 (inactive or
             moderately active);

          -  have a writing medical permission to participate in the training program.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  cognitive impairment (Mini-Mental Status Examination score: illiterate 13 points;
             elementary and middle school 18 points; and high-school 26 points);

          -  inability to respond to verbal command;

          -  pain or other disorders precluding their participation.
